id: pm-y1o4
title: Contracts command lookup should handle package namespace roots
description: The 2026-06-25 source-map audit found that an installed package namespace can expose help at the root command path while pm contracts --command <namespace> reports unknown_command; child command lookup works.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:contracts","area:mcp","area:packages"
created_at: "2026-06-25T04:53:47.719Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-25T13:23:06.409Z"
author: codex-pm-ecosystem-audit-20260625
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: "The intended contract behavior for package namespace roots is defined; pm contracts either returns namespace metadata/child-command guidance for roots like changelog or emits a clearer package-namespace error; regression coverage exercises installed package namespace root and child command; pnpm contracts:check and package command discovery tests pass."
parent: pm-5k4v
repro_steps: "Run node dist/cli.js changelog --help, then node dist/cli.js contracts --command changelog --flags-only --json and node dist/cli.js contracts --command \"changelog generate\" --flags-only --json."
resolution: Implemented command_namespace recovery for package namespace roots in pm contracts and preserved child command contracts for installed package commands.
expected_result: "pm contracts --command <package namespace> gives precise child-command guidance instead of unknown_command, while pm contracts --command '<namespace> <child>' continues to return the child command flags."
actual_result: pm contracts --command changelog now reports command_namespace with concrete changelog export/generate retry examples; changelog generate/export child lookups return extension-provided flag contracts.
